<?xml version="1.0"?>
<block>
  <name>ATA Stream</name>
  <key>ata_ata_stream</key>
  <category>[ATA]</category>
  <import>import grnet</import>
  <!--
  <make>ata.ata_stream($udpport, $ata_header, $payloadsize, $verbose)</make>
  -->
  <make>grnet.udp_source(gr.sizeof_char, 1, $port,$header,$payloadsize,$notifyMissed,False)</make>
  <param>
    <name>UDP Port</name>
    <key>port</key>
    <value>50000</value>
    <type>int</type>
  </param>
  <param>
    <name>Header Format</name>
    <key>header</key>
    <value>4</value>
    <type>int</type>
    <option>
      <name>New Header</name>
      <key>4</key>
    </option>
    <option>
      <name>Old Header</name>
      <key>5</key>
    </option>
  </param>
	<param>
		<name>UDP Packet Data Size</name>
		<key>payloadsize</key>
		<value>4160</value>
		<type>int</type>
	</param>
	<param>
		<name>Notify Missed Frames</name>
		<key>notifyMissed</key>
		<type>enum</type>
		<option>
			<name>No</name>
			<key>False</key>
		</option>
		<option>
			<name>Yes</name>
			<key>True</key>
		</option>
	</param>
  <source>
    <name>out</name>
    <type>byte</type>
  </source>
	<doc>
	This block is a convenience wrapper for a gr-grnet UDP source block specific to ATA data streams.  Data streams come in on two UDP ports: 50000 for x polarization and 50001 for y polarization.  The new packet format has a 4160 payload (4096 + a 64-bit header).
	</doc>
</block>
